	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Yet another shooting has occurred in Cape Town's Facreton area, in spite of protest marches by residents to demand an end to the violence. "The Kensington Community Police Forum confirms that this morning, Saturday the 8th of September, a shooting incident occurred in Factreton," said KCPF spokesperson Zainulabideen van der Schyff. "One male was left wounded in Albacore street and subsequently rushed to hospital for medical assistance. "The Kensington Community Police Forum urges all residents to remain vigilant during these trying times and report all suspicious activity to [the SA Police Service]." READ:'You look in your child's bed and you find empty bullets' - Cape Town residents block road in anti-gang protest Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Andre Traut said an attempted murder case was registered after the victim was shot and wounded at around 11:00. Last month residents of the Kensington and Facreton blocked a major arterial route during rush hour traffic to get national government to pay attention to gang violence and shootings in the area. In July four people in one family were shot and wounded. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  